 haben theologische Deutungen von Schmerz den kulturellen Umgang mit ihm entscheidend mitgeprägt - von der Aufforderung zum Mitleiden über das »mannhafte« Ignorieren des Schmerzes bis zu den unterschiedlichen Bemühungen, Schmerzen zu lindern und seine Ursachen zu heilen.  afunded by Backlisttransformation EOSC Future  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPainxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aSufferingxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 4aLeiden. 4aReligion. 4aReligionsgeschichte. 4aReligionswissenschaft. 4aSchmerz. 4aSusan Sontag. 4aÄsthetik. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aHistory of Religion.  aPain.  aReligion.  aReligious Studies.  aSuffer.1 aBauer, Benedikt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBendemann, Reinhard von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEgo, Beate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEleyth, Nathalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGause, Ute, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGehm, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreschat, Katharina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreschat, Katharina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGöcke, Benedikt Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHöfer, Alena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJahnel, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJahnel, Claudia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJähnichen, Traugott, e